Since B ∪ B is the union of set B with itself, it remains the same set B. Therefore, B ∪ B = {3, 4}.

Now, we need to find the Cartesian product of A x (B ∪ B), which is A x B.

A x B = {(a, b) | a ∈ A, b ∈ B}

A x B = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4)}

So, the Cartesian product A x (B ∪ B) is {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4)}.
